<!-- SECTION 4: WHO CAN FILE -->
<section class="content-section" id="who-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Who Needs to Change Their Auditor?</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p>Mandatory rotation under Section 139(2) applies specifically to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Listed Companies</strong> - companies listed on any recognised stock exchange</li>
                    <li><strong>Unlisted public companies</strong> with paid-up share capital of INR 10 crore or more</li>
                    <li><strong>Private limited companies</strong> with paid-up share capital of INR 20 crore or more</li>
                    <li><strong>Companies with public borrowings</strong> from financial institutions, banks, or public deposits of INR 50 crore or more</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;"><strong>NOT applicable to:</strong> One Person Companies (OPC), Small Companies, and private limited companies below the above thresholds.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:12px;"><strong>All companies</strong> (including those exempt from mandatory rotation) can change their auditor via resignation or removal at any point during the auditor's term.</p>

            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

